{
  "texts": [
    "The parameters were used to analyse the sample in the same way as Koszewski [140] and Münster [141], but with the addition of LoS, as it is an important factor when analyzing environments.",
    "The LoS metric is used to measure the size of the environment.",
    "The 360° environments were separated from free roaming iVR environments for accurate evaluation of the size.",
    "The 360° environments were marked as such before the metric was applied, and together with the free roaming iVR environments were rated on a scale of 1 to 5, based on their size.",
    "Figure 4 provides a visual comparison of the different environment sizes in relation to the size of a person."
  ]
}